definitions: To place a crown on the head of (a monarch) as a symbol of royalty.
To invest officially with royal power or authority.
To be the highest part or top of (something).
To complete or bring to a successful conclusion.
To place a dental crown on (a tooth).
examples: The queen was crowned in Westminster Abbey.
Success in the competition crowned years of effort.
The mountain was crowned with snow.
He crowned his opponent with a swift punch.
The dentist will crown the damaged tooth next week.
